column85: Description
Flat start to the year

Headwind. Some of the Lavender cycling trail - plenty of gravel touring gold - mixed in with the always stunning Pine Hut, Gap and Camel Hump Rds. Budgies and cockatiels on Scenic Rd before Eudunda. Fruit bats on Camac Rd. Frogs and wet clay everywhere.

Headwind till the change came through at Tarlee. Gawler railway single track was new to me and a bonus for heading out north. Lots of stubble quail - didnât hear any on a similar route in early September. Webb Gap campsite steep, rocky and wind blown. Stumbled on Brady Creek Tennis Club while heading to Huppatz Hut instead. Welcome shelter from wind and rain.
